Sentencas: Layered perovskite-structure oxides LaBaCuFeO5+x (LBCFO) and LaBaCuCoO5+x (LBCCO) were prepared and the electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance were investigated as potential cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of LaBaCuFeO5+x and LaBaCuCoO5+x as potential cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of LBCCO is much higher than that of LBCFO.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of LaBaCuFeO5+x and LaBaCuCoO5+x as potential cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Area specific resistances of LBCFO and LBCCO cathode materials on Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte are as low as 0.21 Omega cm(2) and 0.11 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of LaBaCuFeO5+x and LaBaCuCoO5+x as potential cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the LBCFO/SDC/Ni-SDC and LBCCO/SDC/Ni-SDC cells with 300 mu m thick electrolytes attains 557 mW cm(-2) and 603 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of LaBaCuFeO5+x and LaBaCuCoO5+x as potential cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Preliminary results demonstrated that the layered perovskite-structure oxides LBCFO and LBCCO are very promising cathode materials for application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical performances of LaBaCuFeO5+x and LaBaCuCoO5+x as potential cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
